248
00:58:44.840 --> 00:58:47.510
I wanna help you. but you have to let me in.

249
00:59:05.010 --> 00:59:06.880
A signal.

250
00:59:08.550 --> 00:59:10.830
Maybe if I can get a signal.

251
00:59:11.710 --> 00:59:13.530
They can track me.

252
00:59:15.310 --> 00:59:17.130
Find me.

253
00:59:32.480 --> 00:59:35.030
Come on. Come on.

254
00:59:35.110 --> 00:59:37.270
- Oh. crap.
- <i>Yeah. hello?</i>

255
00:59:37.350 --> 00:59:38.900
- Oh. hello.
- <i>Hello?</i>

256
00:59:38.980 --> 00:59:41.960
Hi. Tony. This is Susan LeMarque.

257
00:59:42.040 --> 00:59:44.830
- I'm Eric's mother.
- <i>Hey.</i>

258
00:59:44.910 --> 00:59:49.300
Yes. hi. I know that we haven't
spoken much. because. well. anyway...

259
00:59:49.380 --> 00:59:52.300
...I know he's talked about you.
about snowboarding.

260
00:59:52.380 --> 00:59:56.730
And... he's up in Winter Haven.
or he was the last time I spoke to him...

261
00:59:56.810 --> 00:59:59.970
...but he's missed
a very important court date.

262
01:00:00.050 --> 01:00:02.930
And I'm very worried about him.
and I haven't spoken to him in six days.

263
01:00:03.010 --> 01:00:06.000
- <i>What's this have to do with me?</i>
- I was wondering if he'd reached out to you.

264
01:00:06.080 --> 01:00:10.000
- <i>Yeah. I called him when he was up there.</i>
- You did? When was that?

265
01:00:10.080 --> 01:00:13.860
- <i>It was Thursday.</i>
- I see. Do you have an address for him?

266
01:00:13.940 --> 01:00:16.950
- <i>Yeah. let me look.</i>
- Fantastic.

267
01:00:17.030 --> 01:00:18.940
- <i>He's at the Winter Haven cabin.</i>
- Great.

268
01:00:19.020 --> 01:00:21.530
- <i>Very easy to find.</i>
- This is wonderful. Tony.

269
01:00:21.610 --> 01:00:24.060
More than you can know. Thank you so much.

270
01:00:24.140 --> 01:00:25.460
<i>Yeah. yeah.</i>

271
01:02:43.910 --> 01:02:47.330
Oh. please. please. don't let me
find him lying on the floor.

272
01:02:48.110 --> 01:02:49.620
Please.

273
01:02:52.240 --> 01:02:55.290
Eric? Eric?

274
01:02:56.480 --> 01:02:58.060
What?

275
01:02:58.340 --> 01:02:59.920
Eric!

276
01:03:06.400 --> 01:03:08.490
His clothes are still here.

277
01:03:17.900 --> 01:03:19.760
Damn it.

278
01:03:28.440 --> 01:03:29.960
Eric!

279
01:03:43.740 --> 01:03:45.590
- Sarah. risk management.
- Susan.

280
01:03:45.670 --> 01:03:47.550
Nice to meet you.

281
01:03:48.270 --> 01:03:51.700
So. exactly how long has it been
since you last saw your son?

282
01:03:51.780 --> 01:03:54.300
Seven days. I went to the cabin
where he was staying...

283
01:03:54.380 --> 01:03:58.110
...and there was no phone. wallet or keys.
but everything else was there.

284
01:03:58.190 --> 01:04:00.590
And when you last heard from him.
you're sure he was here?

285
01:04:00.670 --> 01:04:04.530
Oh. yes. yes. he left me a message.
I just didn't hear my phone.

286
01:04:04.610 --> 01:04:08.110
Okay. the first thing we do in this situation
is we file a missing persons report...

287
01:04:08.190 --> 01:04:09.510
...with the sheriff's office.

288
01:04:09.590 --> 01:04:12.280
Then if they don't have any leads.
I'll call Search and Rescue.

289
01:04:12.360 --> 01:04:15.240
The process will probably
take about a day or two.

290
01:04:15.320 --> 01:04:17.570
No. no. Sarah. you don't understand.

291
01:04:17.650 --> 01:04:21.060
My son had a court date
yesterday that he missed. Okay?

292
01:04:21.140 --> 01:04:24.380
And that message he left me.
that was not normal...

293
01:04:24.450 --> 01:04:27.270
...him telling me where he was
and what he was doing.

294
01:04:27.350 --> 01:04:30.690
He never does that. never.
You wanna know why he did it?

295
01:04:30.770 --> 01:04:34.010
Because he was letting me know that
he was gonna make it to the court date...

296
01:04:34.090 --> 01:04:36.170
...he was getting it together.

297
01:04:36.250 --> 01:04:39.640
So when I walk into that courtroom
and he is not there...

298
01:04:39.720 --> 01:04:42.570
...and then I walk into that cabin
and I see his clothes...

299
01:04:42.650 --> 01:04:47.310
...and old congealed food
sitting there and no him?

300
01:04:47.390 --> 01:04:51.380
I can't wait a day or two.
and if he is out there in that snow...

301
01:04:51.460 --> 01:04:53.670
...on that mountain. neither can he.

302
01:04:55.920 --> 01:04:59.960
- Okay. you have a photo?
- Yes. yes. I do.

303
01:05:03.190 --> 01:05:05.460
- <i>Search and Rescue.</i>
- Search and Rescue?

304
01:05:05.540 --> 01:05:08.440
Yeah. this is RM down at Winter Haven.
I need to report a missing person.

305
01:05:08.520 --> 01:05:10.490
- <i>What's the name?</i>
- Full name?

306
01:05:10.570 --> 01:05:12.780
Eric LeMarque.

307
01:05:12.860 --> 01:05:15.840
- Eric... Eric LeMarque.
- <i>How long has he been missing?</i>

308
01:05:15.920 --> 01:05:17.870
- Seven days ago.
- <i>You have a photo?</i>

309
01:05:17.950 --> 01:05:20.240
Yeah. I'm getting the photo now.

310
01:05:24.420 --> 01:05:26.710
I'm gonna need Search and Rescue
on the helipad in 15 minutes.

311
01:05:26.790 --> 01:05:28.810
- <i>Fifteen. copy.</i>
- Thank you.

312
01:05:28.890 --> 01:05:31.340
- You know my son?
- Walk with me.

313
01:05:31.420 --> 01:05:33.870
- You've met my son?
- I've met your son. okay?

314
01:05:33.950 --> 01:05:36.370
I gave him a ride up the mountain
7 days ago. but that's all I know.

315
01:05:36.450 --> 01:05:38.710
Right now I'm just trying
to take precautions.

316
01:05:38.790 --> 01:05:41.310
Corey. get the whole team searching
for anything with radio comms.

317
01:05:41.390 --> 01:05:45.020
I'm talking about cell phones. FM/AM radios.
anything that's gonna receive a signal.

318
01:05:45.100 --> 01:05:45.970
You got it.

319
01:05:46.050 --> 01:05:48.010
Hopefully. he'll get
to the top of the mountain.

320
01:05:48.090 --> 01:05:50.140
You think he's up there?

321
01:05:52.090 --> 01:05:53.950
I know he's up there.

322
01:05:57.920 --> 01:06:00.370
- Ready to go?
- Yeah. let's go.

323
01:06:15.220 --> 01:06:17.930
<i>Patrol 1. Search and Rescue in progress.</i>

324
01:06:18.010 --> 01:06:20.910
White male. 6' 3" tall.

325
01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:33.840
Curt. anything come up yet?

326
01:06:34.520 --> 01:06:38.740
FM. AM. cell. Nothing. T-cast is clear.

327
01:07:06.770 --> 01:07:09.990
<i>We've got 15 minutes till we lose visibility.</i>

328
01:08:11.820 --> 01:08:13.400
Wait!

329
01:08:14.680 --> 01:08:16.260
Wait!

330
01:08:19.050 --> 01:08:21.300
Wait! Wait!

331
01:08:26.420 --> 01:08:28.040
Wait!

332
01:08:36.990 --> 01:08:38.530
Wait!

333
01:08:41.550 --> 01:08:43.130
Wait!

334
01:08:46.890 --> 01:08:49.220
Wait! Wait!

335
01:08:55.320 --> 01:08:56.830
Wait!

336
01:10:00.050 --> 01:10:03.300
Sarah. we have to call it.

337
01:10:31.510 --> 01:10:35.020
<i>I'm sorry. sweetheart. I'm so sorry.</i>

338
01:10:35.410 --> 01:10:37.170
Mama loves you.

339
01:10:37.250 --> 01:10:39.390
With all her heart.

340
01:10:48.010 --> 01:10:49.530
No.

341
01:10:54.320 --> 01:10:56.710
I can't let her find me like this.

342
01:11:03.960 --> 01:11:05.610
Hey.

343
01:11:06.030 --> 01:11:08.840
Thought you might want these.
It gets pretty cold up here.

344
01:11:08.920 --> 01:11:12.370
- That's very kind.
- You must definitely want that back.

345
01:11:12.850 --> 01:11:15.120
Yes. definitely. thank you.

346
01:11:17.710 --> 01:11:20.330
You know. as soon as the sun
comes up. we'll be back up there.

347
01:11:21.850 --> 01:11:25.830
What about tonight?
What's Eric gonna do out there tonight?

348
01:11:25.910 --> 01:11:28.510
If I take my team out there tonight.
this becomes a rescue mission...

349
01:11:28.590 --> 01:11:30.500
...for more than one person.

350
01:11:30.580 --> 01:11:33.070
I can't risk that. I'm sorry.

351
01:11:37.260 --> 01:11:39.920
Are you close with your mother. Sarah?

352
01:11:40.650 --> 01:11:42.120
Sometimes.

353
01:11:44.310 --> 01:11:47.530
Bet you call her like once...

354
01:11:47.610 --> 01:11:51.070
...every other week or so. if that much.

355
01:11:51.810 --> 01:11:54.690
I can guarantee you
that those seven minutes...

356
01:11:54.770 --> 01:11:57.590
...are the highlight of her month.

357
01:11:58.300 --> 01:12:01.470
Because then she gets to feel like
she's a part of your life again.

358
01:12:02.650 --> 01:12:05.160
'Cause she still remembers
when you were little and...

359
01:12:05.250 --> 01:12:07.450
...she would hold you
and sing you to sleep...

360
01:12:07.530 --> 01:12:10.820
...and it was the happiest time of her life.

361
01:12:13.770 --> 01:12:16.300
I just want you to imagine. God forbid.

362
01:12:16.380 --> 01:12:20.770
...something should happen to you in your
line of work and you were no longer here.

363
01:12:20.850 --> 01:12:24.670
Your mother's life would essentially be over.

364
01:12:25.440 --> 01:12:28.060
Her heart would be an empty hole.

365
01:12:29.310 --> 01:12:31.600
I just need you to understand.

366
01:12:32.440 --> 01:12:34.860
You have to find my son.

367
01:12:35.580 --> 01:12:37.260
Please.

368
01:12:39.650 --> 01:12:41.460
You have to find him.

369
01:14:54.210 --> 01:14:56.260
Gotta make it to the top.

370
01:15:20.240 --> 01:15:24.090
Hey. this has been the coldest
winter we've had in ten years.

371
01:15:24.630 --> 01:15:26.200
Three. four days tops.

372
01:15:26.280 --> 01:15:29.960
That's the longest someone could survive
out there in these conditions.

373
01:15:30.040 --> 01:15:32.120
I'll call the report in.

374
01:15:32.470 --> 01:15:34.100
Thanks.

375
01:15:36.680 --> 01:15:38.760
Comm Center from Life Flight.

376
01:15:38.840 --> 01:15:40.820
<i>Go from Comm Center.</i>

377
01:15:40.900 --> 01:15:44.720
You can cancel Search and Rescue.
This is gonna be a body recovery.

378
01:17:12.000 --> 01:17:14.090
About 12 more steps.

379
01:19:01.040 --> 01:19:02.820
<i>All right. results are in.</i>

380
01:19:02.900 --> 01:19:07.180
<i>Your kids made the snowmen you sent us
to our radio station's website...</i>

381
01:19:08.030 --> 01:19:10.320
Hey. guys. can you excuse me for a minute?

382
01:19:10.400 --> 01:19:12.180
<i>We have some late-breaking information.</i>

383
01:19:12.260 --> 01:19:15.250
<i>Turns out a face drawn
on the windshield of a car...</i>

384
01:19:15.330 --> 01:19:19.350
<i>...does not count as a snowman.
That is just a car...</i>

385
01:19:32.700 --> 01:19:34.270
Help.

386
01:20:11.530 --> 01:20:13.410
Come on.

387
01:20:19.290 --> 01:20:21.110
Are you kidding me. man?

388
01:20:21.190 --> 01:20:24.280
- The organization dumped me.
- You don't gotta lie to me about it.

389
01:20:24.360 --> 01:20:26.850
I was there at that practice
when you walked away.

390
01:20:26.930 --> 01:20:29.490
You were the future of the franchise.

391
01:20:29.570 --> 01:20:33.200
You were twice as good as I ever was.
Do you understand how frustrating that is?

392
01:20:33.280 --> 01:20:36.700
To watch somebody that has
everything. everything...

393
01:20:36.780 --> 01:20:39.840
...and then you just walk away. You quit!

394
01:20:52.460 --> 01:20:56.490
<i>LeMarque! LeMarque!
What the hell are you doing?</i>

395
01:20:56.570 --> 01:21:00.690
<i>It's not I. it's we. It's the crest on
the front. not the name on the back.</i>

396
01:21:00.770 --> 01:21:03.330
You're gonna have to figure that out.

397
01:21:03.410 --> 01:21:06.010
Now. today. get off my ice.

398
01:21:06.090 --> 01:21:09.110
Beat it! I've had enough of you.
You're done for the day.

399
01:21:09.790 --> 01:21:11.450
Get off my ice.

400
01:21:12.330 --> 01:21:14.180
You're right.

401
01:21:14.960 --> 01:21:16.820
I am done.

402
01:21:19.800 --> 01:21:21.800
Don't even think about it.

403
01:21:21.880 --> 01:21:24.110
That's a one-way ticket. pal.

404
01:21:29.590 --> 01:21:32.950
- Dad! Dad?
- No. Eric. Don't go after him.

405
01:21:33.030 --> 01:21:34.500
Dad!

406
01:21:35.430 --> 01:21:37.080
Dad!

407
01:21:37.930 --> 01:21:40.010
Where are you going. Dad?

408
01:21:40.090 --> 01:21:42.420
Dad! You can't go!

409
01:21:42.500 --> 01:21:44.990
You can't leave!

410
01:21:45.070 --> 01:21:47.910
Open the door right now. You can't go!

411
01:21:47.990 --> 01:21:49.880
Come here. baby.

412
01:21:52.300 --> 01:21:53.820
Where are you going?

413
01:21:54.600 --> 01:21:57.880
You can't leave your own son. you coward!

414
01:21:59.060 --> 01:22:00.610
No!

415
01:22:02.060 --> 01:22:04.450
What are you doing? Wait!

416
01:22:04.570 --> 01:22:06.420
Don't do it!

417
01:22:09.130 --> 01:22:10.680
Dad!

418
01:22:34.930 --> 01:22:38.750
<i>This isn't my fault! They took my skates!</i>

419
01:22:38.830 --> 01:22:41.420
Stop pointing this at everybody else.

420
01:22:41.500 --> 01:22:44.710
Because you do that in life. it is gonna
hurt a whole lot worse than this...

421
01:22:44.790 --> 01:22:46.620
...do you understand me?

422
01:22:47.090 --> 01:22:49.540
- Do you understand me?
- Yes. sir.

423
01:22:51.830 --> 01:22:54.310
The whole world's wondering. LeMarque...

424
01:23:01.760 --> 01:23:03.790
...why'd ya quit?

425
01:23:58.760 --> 01:24:02.250
<i>Spencer and his snowman. is that huge!</i>

426
01:24:02.330 --> 01:24:04.610
<i>That is... that is a lot of snow...</i>

427
01:25:27.360 --> 01:25:29.210
Hi. Mom.

428
01:25:33.920 --> 01:25:35.810
It's me.

429
01:25:39.020 --> 01:25:41.880
I don't really know what it is I wanna say.

430
01:25:45.850 --> 01:25:48.670
But I don't think I have too much time. so...

431
01:25:58.090 --> 01:26:01.540
...I just want you to know
that I'm okay without those things.

432
01:26:13.150 --> 01:26:16.010
And that I... I'm sorry.

433
01:26:20.960 --> 01:26:23.000
I'm sorry for everything.

434
01:26:31.650 --> 01:26:34.700
Turns out I'm a bit of a coward myself.

435
01:26:59.890 --> 01:27:01.770
It's funny.

436
01:27:05.440 --> 01:27:08.120
We only get to live life forward.

437
01:27:11.320 --> 01:27:14.770
But it never makes any sense
until we're looking back.

438
01:27:30.020 --> 01:27:33.540
I need you to know that we've
canceled the search and rescue.

439
01:27:33.620 --> 01:27:35.240
Why?

440
01:27:35.620 --> 01:27:38.050
We've now ruled this a body recovery.

441
01:27:45.990 --> 01:27:47.840
I love you. Mom.

442
01:29:18.150 --> 01:29:20.970
Hey. Sarah. we just had a signal pop up.

443
01:29:22.770 --> 01:29:26.380
Wait. wait. hold on a minute. We just had
a signal popped up and then it disappeared.

444
01:29:26.460 --> 01:29:28.540
- Where?
- Mount Widow's Peak.

445
01:29:28.620 --> 01:29:30.070
- But it wasn't one of ours.
- You sure?

446
01:29:30.150 --> 01:29:32.840
- Yeah. positive.
- Search and Rescue. this is RM.

447
01:29:32.920 --> 01:29:35.380
We just picked up a signal
on Mount Widow's Peak.

448
01:29:49.180 --> 01:29:55.180
<i>Coordinates are North 4-0-3-2-3-0.60...</i>

449
01:29:55.260 --> 01:30:01.030
...west 111-4-1-3.07.

450
01:30:11.350 --> 01:30:13.200
Hold on. Eric.

451
01:30:33.220 --> 01:30:34.930
Hey. got him!

452
01:30:35.010 --> 01:30:37.020
Up on that ridge. two o'clock.

453
01:31:21.250 --> 01:31:24.400
Please. let him be alive.
Please. let him be alive.

454
01:31:24.480 --> 01:31:26.380
Please. let him be alive.

455
01:31:55.210 --> 01:31:59.070
Search and Rescue to base.
Two minutes out before landing.

456
01:32:20.780 --> 01:32:23.460
You're going to be okay. Eric.
You're going to be okay.

457
01:32:57.350 --> 01:32:58.910
Eric!

458
01:33:02.340 --> 01:33:04.390
You're alive!

459
01:33:08.010 --> 01:33:10.300
I love you. sweetheart!

460
01:33:12.280 --> 01:33:15.600
<i>Sometimes you get hit. You fall.</i>

461
01:33:15.680 --> 01:33:17.740
<i>You can't get back up.</i>

462
01:33:18.560 --> 01:33:20.440
<i>And you fall further.</i>

463
01:33:22.550 --> 01:33:25.820
<i>Before the mountain.
I couldn't see how far I'd fallen.</i>

464
01:33:27.110 --> 01:33:29.370
<i>Maybe that's what I had to go through...</i>

465
01:33:29.450 --> 01:33:31.280
<i>...to finally live.</i>

466
01:33:34.240 --> 01:33:36.700
<i>Sometimes a part of yourself has to die...</i>

467
01:33:36.780 --> 01:33:38.940
<i>...maybe even the part you love most...</i>

468
01:33:39.020 --> 01:33:41.480
...before you can realize
what makes you whole...

469
01:33:41.560 --> 01:33:45.210
...and clearly see that it's larger than us.

470
01:33:46.050 --> 01:33:49.810
If you're in the dark. get through it
by seeing the invisible...

471
01:33:49.890 --> 01:33:52.010
...so that you can do the impossible.

472
01:33:52.390 --> 01:33:55.580
Be responsible and accountable for yourself.

473
01:33:55.660 --> 01:33:57.100
Just fail forward.

474
01:33:57.180 --> 01:34:00.660
It will all make sense when you see
the light at the break of dawn.

474
01:34:01.305 --> 01:35:01.410
